In this example, we'll read a text file line by line and count the number of occurrences of the word "apple" in the file.

The first step is to include the appropriate headers, such as this:

```
#include <fstream>
#include <iostream>

int main() {
  std::ifstream file("apple.txt");
  std::string word;
  int count = 0;

  while (file >> word) {
    count++;
  }

  std::cout << "There are " << count << " occurrences of the word \"apple\" in the file." << std::endl;
}
